README.md
     1→# humanize
    12→This modest package contains various common humanization utilities, like turning a
    13→number into a fuzzy human-readable duration ("3 minutes ago") or into a human-readable
    14→size or throughput. It is localized to:
    15→
    16→- Arabic
    17→- Basque
    18→- Bengali
    19→- Brazilian Portuguese
    20→- Catalan
    21→- Danish
    22→- Dutch
    23→- Esperanto
    24→- European Portuguese
    25→- Finnish
    26→- French
    27→- German
    28→- Greek
    29→- Hebrew
    30→- Indonesian
    31→- Italian
    32→- Japanese
    33→- Klingon
    34→- Korean
    35→- Norwegian
    36→- Persian
    37→- Polish
    38→- Russian
    39→- Simplified Chinese
    40→- Slovak
    41→- Slovenian
    42→- Spanish
    43→- Swedish
    44→- Turkish
    45→- Ukrainian
    46→- Uzbek
    47→- Vietnamese
    48→
    49→## API reference
    51→[https://humanize.readthedocs.io](https://humanize.readthedocs.io/)
    52→
    53→<!-- usage-start -->
    54→
    55→## Installation
    57→### From PyPI
    59→```bash
    60→python3 -m pip install --upgrade humanize
    61→```
    62→
    63→### From source
    65→```bash
    66→git clone https://github.com/python-humanize/humanize
    67→cd humanize
    68→python3 -m pip install -e .
    69→```
    70→
    71→## Usage
    73→### Integer humanization
    75→```pycon
    76→>>> import humanize
    77→>>> humanize.intcomma(12345)
    78→'12,345'
    79→>>> humanize.intword(123455913)
    80→'123.5 million'
    81→>>> humanize.intword(12345591313)
    82→'12.3 billion'
    83→>>> humanize.apnumber(4)
    84→'four'
    85→>>> humanize.apnumber(41)
    86→'41'
    87→```
    88→
    89→### Date & time humanization
    91→```pycon
    92→>>> import humanize
    93→>>> import datetime as dt
    94→>>> humanize.naturalday(dt.datetime.now())
    95→'today'
    96→>>> humanize.naturaldelta(dt.timedelta(seconds=1001))
    97→'16 minutes'
    98→>>> humanize.naturalday(dt.datetime.now() - dt.timedelta(days=1))
    99→'yesterday'
   100→>>> humanize.naturalday(dt.date(2007, 6, 5))
   101→'Jun 05'
   102→>>> humanize.naturaldate(dt.date(2007, 6, 5))
   103→'Jun 05 2007'
   104→>>> humanize.naturaltime(dt.datetime.now() - dt.timedelta(seconds=1))
   105→'a second ago'
   106→>>> humanize.naturaltime(dt.datetime.now() - dt.timedelta(seconds=3600))
   107→'an hour ago'
   108→```
   109→
   110→### Precise time delta
   112→```pycon
   113→>>> import humanize
   114→>>> import datetime as dt
   115→>>> delta = dt.timedelta(seconds=3633, days=2, microseconds=123000)
   116→>>> humanize.precisedelta(delta)
   117→'2 days, 1 hour and 33.12 seconds'
   118→>>> humanize.precisedelta(delta, minimum_unit="microseconds")
   119→'2 days, 1 hour, 33 seconds and 123 milliseconds'
   120→>>> humanize.precisedelta(delta, suppress=["days"], format="%0.4f")
   121→'49 hours and 33.1230 seconds'
   122→```
   123→
   124→#### Smaller units
   126→If seconds are too large, set `minimum_unit` to milliseconds or microseconds:
   127→
   128→```pycon
   129→>>> import humanize
   130→>>> import datetime as dt
   131→>>> humanize.naturaldelta(dt.timedelta(seconds=2))
   132→'2 seconds'
   133→```
   134→
   135→```pycon
   136→>>> delta = dt.timedelta(milliseconds=4)
   137→>>> humanize.naturaldelta(delta)
   138→'a moment'
   139→>>> humanize.naturaldelta(delta, minimum_unit="milliseconds")
   140→'4 milliseconds'
   141→>>> humanize.naturaldelta(delta, minimum_unit="microseconds")
   142→'4 milliseconds'
   143→```
   144→
   145→```pycon
   146→>>> humanize.naturaltime(delta)
   147→'now'
   148→>>> humanize.naturaltime(delta, minimum_unit="milliseconds")
   149→'4 milliseconds ago'
   150→>>> humanize.naturaltime(delta, minimum_unit="microseconds")
   151→'4 milliseconds ago'
   152→```
   153→
   154→### File size humanization
   156→```pycon
   157→>>> import humanize
   158→>>> humanize.naturalsize(1_000_000)
   159→'1.0 MB'
   160→>>> humanize.naturalsize(1_000_000, binary=True)
   161→'976.6 KiB'
   162→>>> humanize.naturalsize(1_000_000, gnu=True)
   163→'976.6K'
   164→```
   165→
   166→### Human-readable floating point numbers
   168→```pycon
   169→>>> import humanize
   170→>>> humanize.fractional(1/3)
   171→'1/3'
   172→>>> humanize.fractional(1.5)
   173→'1 1/2'
   174→>>> humanize.fractional(0.3)
   175→'3/10'
   176→>>> humanize.fractional(0.333)
   177→'333/1000'
   178→>>> humanize.fractional(1)
   179→'1'
   180→```
   181→
   182→### Scientific notation
   184→```pycon
   185→>>> import humanize
   186→>>> humanize.scientific(0.3)
   187→'3.00 x 10⁻¹'
   188→>>> humanize.scientific(500)
   189→'5.00 x 10²'
   190→>>> humanize.scientific("20000")
   191→'2.00 x 10⁴'
   192→>>> humanize.scientific(1**10)
   193→'1.00 x 10⁰'
   194→>>> humanize.scientific(1**10, precision=1)
   195→'1.0 x 10⁰'
   196→>>> humanize.scientific(1**10, precision=0)
   197→'1 x 10⁰'
   198→```
   199→
   200→## Localization
   202→How to change locale at runtime:
   203→
   204→```pycon
   205→>>> import humanize
   206→>>> import datetime as dt
   207→>>> humanize.naturaltime(dt.timedelta(seconds=3))
   208→'3 seconds ago'
   209→>>> _t = humanize.i18n.activate("ru_RU")
   210→>>> humanize.naturaltime(dt.timedelta(seconds=3))
   211→'3 секунды назад'
   212→>>> humanize.i18n.deactivate()
   213→>>> humanize.naturaltime(dt.timedelta(seconds=3))
   214→'3 seconds ago'
   215→```
   216→
   217→You can pass additional parameter `path` to `activate` to specify a path to search
   218→locales in.
   219→
   220→```pycon
   221→>>> import humanize
   222→>>> humanize.i18n.activate("xx_XX")
   223→<...>
   224→FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No translation file found for domain: 'humanize'
   225→>>> humanize.i18n.activate("pt_BR", path="path/to/my/own/translation/")
   226→<gettext.GNUTranslations instance ...>
   227→```
   228→
   229→<!-- usage-end -->
   230→
   231→How to add new phrases to existing locale files:
   232→
   233→```sh
   234→xgettext --from-code=UTF-8 -o humanize.pot -k'_' -k'N_' -k'P_:1c,2' -k'NS_:1,2' -k'_ngettext:1,2' -l python src/humanize/*.py  # extract new phrases
   235→msgmerge -U src/humanize/locale/ru_RU/LC_MESSAGES/humanize.po humanize.pot # add them to locale files
   236→```
   237→
   238→How to add a new locale:
   239→
   240→```sh
   241→msginit -i humanize.pot -o humanize/locale/<locale name>/LC_MESSAGES/humanize.po --locale <locale name>
   242→```
   243→
   244→Where `<locale name>` is a locale abbreviation, eg. `en_GB`, `pt_BR` or just `ru`, `fr`
   245→etc.
   246→
   247→List the language at the top of this README.

